    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style and culture of a group that originated in the Tewa culture and who have inhabited the area around the current Nambé Pueblo since the 14th century. The term is from Tewa, meaning "People of the Round Earth."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
